          },
        ] as Reason[],
        faqs: [
          {
            q: 'Is ROSA GDPR compliant for regulated European workloads?',
            a: "ROSA runs on AWS infrastructure — a US company subject to the US CLOUD Act. While AWS has EU regions, data sovereignty concerns persist under GDPR, DORA and NIS2. Stakater Cloud is operated by Stakater AB (Sweden) with all data hosted in the Netherlands. No US parent company, no CLOUD Act exposure.",
          },
          {
            q: 'Does ROSA include GitOps, CI/CD or observability tooling?',
            a: "No. ROSA manages the OpenShift control plane. Everything above it — ArgoCD, Tekton, Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, Jaeger, OpenBao, multi-tenancy — you must install, configure and maintain yourself. Stakater Cloud's KubeStack+ tier includes all of this pre-wired and managed from day one.",
          },
          {
            q: 'How does ROSA pricing compare to Stakater Cloud?',
            a: "ROSA pricing is EC2 node costs plus Red Hat OpenShift licensing plus any platform tooling you add on top. It scales unpredictably and often requires dedicated cloud cost management. Stakater Cloud is a flat monthly subscription from €888/month — one invoice, no per-resource surprises.",
          },
          {
            q: 'What support do I get for platform tooling with ROSA?',
            a: "ROSA support covers the OpenShift cluster itself. Issues with your GitOps setup, CI/CD pipelines, secrets management or observability stack fall outside ROSA's scope — you are on your own or rely on separate vendors. With Stakater Cloud, the entire platform is our responsibility under one SLA.",
          },
          {
            q: 'How quickly can I get a production-ready cluster with Stakater Cloud?',
            a: "ROSA cluster provisioning takes 30–45 minutes. Then you still need to configure your platform tooling, which typically takes weeks to months. Stakater Cloud is production-ready in under 15 minutes — cluster provisioned, GitOps wired, observability running, your team can deploy immediately.",
          },
          {
            q: 'Can I migrate from ROSA to Stakater Cloud?',
            a: "Yes. We help teams move from ROSA and other managed OpenShift platforms. Book a call and we will assess your workloads, data volumes and compliance requirements — and give you an honest estimate of what the migration involves for your specific setup.",
          },
        ] as FAQ[],
      },
    },
    {
      params: { slug: 'eks-alternative' },
      props: {
        competitor: 'EKS',
        fullName: 'Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (EKS)',
        metaDescription: 'Stakater Cloud vs EKS — managed OpenShift with a complete developer platform in the EU vs raw Kubernetes on AWS. No platform team, no AWS lock-in, production-ready in 15 minutes.',
