        heroSubline: 'EKS gives you a Kubernetes control plane on AWS. Stakater Cloud gives you managed OpenShift plus the entire platform layer — GitOps, CI/CD, secrets, observability, multi-tenancy — pre-wired and hosted in the EU.',
        clusterType: 'Managed Kubernetes (AWS)',
        whatIsCompetitor: "EKS is Amazon's managed Kubernetes service. It provisions and patches your Kubernetes control plane on AWS — but GitOps, CI/CD, secrets management, observability, multi-tenancy, security hardening and every other piece of your platform is your team's responsibility to build and operate.",
