        faqs: [
          {
            q: 'Is EKS the same as OpenShift?',
            a: "No. EKS is managed Kubernetes on AWS. OpenShift is an enterprise application platform built on Kubernetes — it adds security hardening, a developer console, integrated image registry, stricter RBAC defaults, developer tooling, and enterprise support from Red Hat. Running OpenShift workloads on EKS requires significant additional configuration.",
          },
          {
            q: 'What do I need to add to EKS to make it production-ready?',
            a: "Quite a lot: a GitOps tool (ArgoCD), CI/CD (Tekton or Jenkins), secrets management (OpenBao or Vault), observability (Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, Jaeger), multi-tenancy enforcement, network policies, image scanning (RHACS), backup (Velero), certificate management. Stakater Cloud includes all of this pre-configured and managed.",
          },
          {
            q: 'Is EKS suitable for GDPR and DORA compliance?',
            a: "EKS runs on AWS — a US company subject to the US CLOUD Act. For European regulated industries under GDPR, DORA or NIS2, this creates data sovereignty concerns. Stakater Cloud provides unambiguous EU data residency: Netherlands data center, operated by Stakater AB (Sweden), ISO 27001:2022 certified.",
          },
          {
            q: 'What does EKS actually cost vs Stakater Cloud?',
            a: "EKS charges per cluster per hour, plus EC2 node costs, load balancers, storage and data transfer. Most teams spend significantly more than they expect once platform tooling is factored in. Stakater Cloud starts at €888/month all in — platform included, no hidden per-resource fees.",
          },
          {
            q: 'How long does it take to go from EKS to production?',
            a: "EKS cluster creation takes minutes. Building a production-grade platform on top — with GitOps, CI/CD, observability, multi-tenancy and security hardening — realistically takes 3–9 months. Stakater Cloud is production-ready in under 15 minutes.",
          },
          {
            q: 'Do I need a dedicated platform engineering team for EKS?',
            a: "In practice, yes. EKS gives you Kubernetes — everything above it requires specialists to build, maintain and evolve. Most teams end up hiring 2–4 platform engineers. Stakater Cloud is your platform team, included in your subscription. Your developers focus on shipping product.",
          },
        ] as FAQ[],
      },
    },
    {
      params: { slug: 'aks-alternative' },
      props: {
        competitor: 'AKS',
        fullName: 'Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)',
        metaDescription: 'Stakater Cloud vs AKS — managed OpenShift with complete developer platform in the EU vs Azure Kubernetes. No platform team needed, GDPR/DORA ready, production in 15 minutes.',
        heroHeadline: 'OpenShift over Kubernetes. Platform over infrastructure.',
        heroSubline: 'AKS manages your Kubernetes cluster on Azure. Stakater Cloud delivers managed OpenShift with GitOps, CI/CD, full observability and more — pre-wired, EU-hosted, operated by Red Hat Premier Partner engineers.',
        clusterType: 'Managed Kubernetes (Azure)',
        whatIsCompetitor: "AKS is Microsoft's managed Kubernetes service on Azure. It provisions and patches your Kubernetes cluster — but the entire developer platform above Kubernetes, including GitOps, CI/CD, secrets, observability, multi-tenancy and compliance tooling, is left entirely to your team.",
        threeReasons: [
          {
            title: 'Enterprise OpenShift over plain Kubernetes',
            body: 'AKS gives you upstream Kubernetes. OpenShift adds enterprise security hardening, a developer-friendly console, integrated image registry, stricter security defaults and enterprise support — making it the preferred choice for European enterprises in finance, healthcare and critical infrastructure.',
            icon: 'M9 12l2 2 4-4M7.835 4.697a3.42 3.42 0 001.946-.806 3.42 3.42 0 014.438 0 3.42 3.42 0 001.946.806 3.42 3.42 0 013.138 3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00.806 1.946 3.42 3.42 0 010 4.438 3.42 3.42 0 00-.806 1.946 3.42 3.42 0 01-3.138 3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00-1.946.806 3.42 3.42 0 01-4.438 0 3.42 3.42 0 00-1.946-.806 3.42 3.42 0 01-3.138-3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00-.806-1.946 3.42 3.42 0 010-4.438 3.42 3.42 0 00.806-1.946 3.42 3.42 0 013.138-3.138z',
