          {
            q: 'Can I migrate from AKS to Stakater Cloud?',
            a: "Yes. We help teams migrate containerised workloads from AKS and other platforms. Book a call and we will scope the migration effort for your specific workloads, compliance requirements and timeline — and tell you honestly what it takes.",
          },
        ] as FAQ[],
      },
    },
    {
      params: { slug: 'gke-alternative' },
      props: {
        competitor: 'GKE',
        fullName: 'Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE)',
        metaDescription: 'Stakater Cloud vs GKE — managed OpenShift with complete developer platform in the EU vs Google Kubernetes Engine. GDPR/DORA/NIS2 compliant, no platform team needed.',
        heroHeadline: 'Enterprise OpenShift in Europe. Everything included.',
        heroSubline: "GKE manages Kubernetes on Google Cloud — the platform layer is still yours to build. Stakater Cloud delivers managed OpenShift with GitOps, CI/CD, full observability and more, hosted in the EU, managed by Red Hat Premier Partners.",
        clusterType: 'Managed Kubernetes (GCP)',
        whatIsCompetitor: "GKE is Google Cloud's managed Kubernetes service. Standard GKE manages the control plane; Autopilot mode removes node management overhead. But the application platform layer — GitOps, CI/CD, secrets, observability, multi-tenancy, compliance tooling — remains your team's responsibility in both modes.",
        threeReasons: [
          {
            title: 'OpenShift over Kubernetes — built for enterprise from the start',
            body: 'GKE gives you managed Kubernetes. OpenShift adds enterprise-grade security hardening, a developer-friendly console, stricter RBAC defaults, integrated image management and enterprise support. For European enterprises running regulated workloads, OpenShift is the stronger starting point.',
            icon: 'M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-2 10v-5a1 1 0 00-1-1h-4a1 1 0 00-1 1v5m6 0H9',
